1 - e^{-x^2} < 1
0 < x \leq 1
e^{-x^2} = 1 - x^2 + \dfrac{x^4}{2!} - \dots 
\dfrac{1 - e^{-x^2}}{x} = x - \dfrac{x^3}{2!} + \dfrac{x^5}{3!} - \dots 
x^n < x^m
n > m
