f(x) = -e^{-x^2}
f'(x) = 2x e^{-x^2}
x = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}
= 2e^{-x^2}(1 - 2x^2)
\eta \in (0,x)
\frac{1 - e^{-x^2}}{x} = \frac{f(x) - f(0)}{x} = f'(\eta) \le f'\left(\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}\right) =  \sqrt{\frac{2}{e}}
